verbs.description: overbuild (third-person singular simple present overbuilds, present participle overbuilding, simple past and past participle overbuilt)

entries.meaning: (transitive, intransitive) To perform excessive construction on a building or in an area.
examples: How much more interesting & worth writing about Betjeman's subjects are than most other modern poets, I mean, whether so-and-so achieves some metaphysical inner unity is not really so interesting to us as the overbuilding of rural Middlesex.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To build over or on top of another structure.
examples: The architect wanted to overbuild the restaurant on top of an office.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To build with excessive size or elaboration.
(intransitive) To construct more buildings than necessary in an area.
